
[1]becoming

   BECOM'ING,ppr., but used rarely or never except as an adjective. Fit;
   suitable; congruous; proper; graceful; belonging to the character, or
   adapted to circumstances; as, he speaks with becoming boldness; a dress
   is very becoming.

   Some writers formerly used of, after this word.

   Such discourses as are becoming of them.

   But this use is inelegant or improper.

   BECOM'ING, a. Ornament. Obs.
